<br>
Me:  &quot;It's not a good idea to shout through the entire zone like that, no one knows were you are&quot;<br>
<br>
Him:  &quot;I'm at the crossroads&quot;<br>
<br>
I do a lookup thinking maybe he's some poor newb who is being killed and he's a 19 ranger! <br>
<br>
Me:  Oh your a 19 ranger you're not in any danger.  Do you have bind wounds?<br>
<br>
Him:  Yes but I only use that in the heat of battle I want someone to come heal me so I can keep getting xp.<br>
<br>
Me:  Well people aren't going to come running through the zone on damand when you shout &quot;heal plz&quot; don't always rely on others to make your life easier.<br>
<br>
Him:  Well you know where I am and my ranger heals suck.<br>
<br>
This is just one example.  Unless you play a druid you cannot possibly understand how many times you get these requests.  I always hear &quot;it's only 60 mana to cast SoW&quot; but typically those saying this are only seeing it from one perspective, there own.  YOUR sow may only cost me 60 mana but how aobut the 10 other requests I've had in the last thirty minutes just because I decided to make a trip to town or go to Black Burrow to work on my faction.  Even anon it doesn't stop the requests and demands from coming in.<br>
<br>
so /rant on<br>
<br>
STOP flaming druids when you don't know what you're talking about!  Get a perspective other than your own for a change!   What about those tanks who complain about casters screaming &quot;on me!!&quot; all the time.  Now that really IS their job when grouped, they don't have to face that outside of it unlike how druids are in demand 24/7.   When I'm on my cleric I remember what my druid goes through and if I truly need a sow (usually because I'm trying to get to a group and have to run through a dangerous area and I know there is no chance I can outrun anything) then I will ask **with respect** something like &quot;I'm so sorry to bother you but could you possibly cast sow on me please I'm a slow cleric and would be glad to donate what I can&quot;.  Thanks to that level of respect, I usually have no problems getting SoW when I need it and most don't accept the donation because they know I am truly in need and that I don't expect it from them.  I'm asking with courtesy and it's their peroggitive to turn me down and I would respect that as well.  If only others would do the same for my druid...<br>
<br>
/rant off<br>
<br>
Let the flaming begin if you like but I believe every word I've said here is absolute truth.  Respect and courtesy get you a long way in this came, try using them.<br>
<br>
Shaladarra Sowtorm *30th season druid*<br>
Gabriarra Mistmoon *30th season cleric*<br>
------------------------------------------<br>
-You inspect Shaladarra-<br>
-You read a note next to all that equipment that says-<br>
&quot;If you're snooping me without the courtesy of asking my permission first there is no WAY i'm giving you anything!&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/userberus00.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Serberus00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/22/01 4:10:31 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: People who complain about people who complain</span><hr size=1> thats a good tactic whenever you need anything, KISS ASS! =)<br>
<br>
typical tells go something like this 'hi, i'm sorry to intrude like this but is there any chance I could get a res? i'd be happy to pick you up and port you directly to my corpse and port you back once your finished, i'd be glad to donate for your time. thank you'<br>
<br>
The key bits to getting this to work is things like typing 'thank you' instead of thx or thanks, it just sounds more sincere, if you request like this then they will respond very pleasantly, they won't always say yes but usually something along the lines of 'sorry, i'm about to go on a planes raid' or something like that.<br>
<br>
The other key factor to getting this to work is making liberal use of the /who all command, look for 55 - 60 clerics who are in zones with a druid ring, somewhere like BB or WC is best because a level 55 - 60 isn't likely to be doing anything.<br>
<br>
A little courtesy and thought on your part can help get things done quickly.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure exactly what my post has to do with the previous one, it sort of morphed as I was thinking about it, but the gist of it is, be pleasant if you want help and your more likely to recieve, and don't sulk like a @#%$ when they turn you down =P<br>
<br>
just reply with a please 'ok, thanks for your time'<br>
<br>
hopefully they'll remember you if they see you in dire straits next time and pop you a res.<br>
<br>
Serberus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugolsec.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Golsec</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/22/01 2:09:35 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.cloudk.clara.net/storage/zidane2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: People who complain about people who complain</span><hr size=1> LOL :)<br>
