(Also known as Cloudien, Druid, The Rathe server)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udobbanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dobbanz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/24/01 9:33:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: People who complain about people who complain</span><hr size=1> Asa druid I know how irratating it is to have somebody just walk up to you and say sow me so I have always made it a point to be incredibly over the top with my courtesy and requests for things like clarity or (god help me) the occaisional rezz. I usually say something along the lines of &quot;Oh great and powerful enchantress, I beg of thee. Grant unto me the gift of clarity and I shall spread word of thy kindness across the face of Norrath.&quot; I even have several versions of that on macros just in case lol. I find I get the clarity or rezz much more often than people who say clarity me or rezz me. I seem to get those more often and faster than the people who even say please lol. So dont discount the value of going over the top when you ask for something, a lot of the time it helps!<br>
