&quot;Ps that also counts for those who ask me for sow or other buffs too. Im much more likely to help out someone when they go crazy with formality lol.&quot; <p><p><center><br><img src="http://www.accesswave.ca/~falwith/Bios/dobbsig.jpg"<br></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukiirlonamaiaeddaen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kiirlona Maiaeddaen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.home.net/la.perdita/Sigs/PerditaI.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/19/01 1:54:22 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/la.perdita/Sigs/Kii1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> In a [very large] nutshell</span><hr size=1> It's all about <i>how</i> and <i>when</i> you ask for a favour.  It's also about <i>where</i> you are too.<br>
<br>
When I zone in and receive a tell from a stranger asking a favour before I even receive my zoning-in message, I am less inclined to do the favour.  Yes, our names appear in /w before we actually land in the zone but it is maddening to zone in to a string of request messages that generate even before you receive the zoning message.  Posing your request very politely can nullify the annoyance factor of receiving messages before fully zoning into an area.<br>
<br>
Don't ask your would-be buffer to run to you, especially if she's an Enchantress or Cleric.<br>
<br>
When I am grouped, I am disinclined to do favours for people not in my group.  If you're grouped nearby and I'm the only one around who can give you the buffs you want, you'd better pay me and my group for the mana.  I'm willing to give SoW or Clarity, but no more than that unless adequately compensated.  Tip: 3p divided amoung a full group for three brain buffs and two body buffs that use 30% of my mana is insufficient.  Suggested donation: 3p for me, the buffer, and 1p for each additional party member.  Oh no, not 8p!  It's so much to a 45+ adventurer who's quad-kiting at KC!<br>
<br>
When I <i>offer</i> to help someone asking for help on /ooc or /shout and he then asks for more than I offer, I'm disinclined to help him.  I'm even more disinclined when he keeps me waiting for five minutes, then says that my help is appreciated but he wants me to help him later.  If you don't want a port right now, don't ask for one right now.  Ask for it when you want it.  Believe it or not, I didn't spend all those months getting to 43 just so I could sit at first torch and wait for your tardy behind.<br>
<br>
And I didn't spend all those months getting to 43 just so I could power-level your lazy behind through the first easy 15 levels of your career either.  I tell you what: I power-level you from 1 to 15 and then you log on your "uber" character and power-level me from 43 to 57.  What?  That seems unreasonable to you?  So sorry.<br>
<br>
Regarding ports and translocations, yes I know that there are some greedy Druids and Wizards out there who charge ridiculous porting and translocating fees.  Is it necessary to argue with them every single time they post their fees?  If you desperately need the port and no one else has advertised, try to politely haggle.  If the price doesn't go down, say thanks but you'll wait.  And don't call the Druid or Wizard mean names if they refuse to port you because they'd like to actually go hunting or work on tradeskills.<br>
<br>
When people spam me with requests, I'm obviously disinclined to do anything other than type /ignore [ idiot's name here ].<br>
<br>
When people ask for a buff using "U" and "plz" I'm disinclined to help.  Yes, it's anal retentive, but I am a roleplayer.  You don't have to bow or kiss my feet, and you need not call me "m'lady," but it won't break your fingers to type out "you" and "please."  I make exceptions towards "sow" and "crack" and "speed", and I think that's reasonably generous.  However, as Dobban notes, going over the top does help--it might get you Skin like Diamond + Strength of Stone or Gift of Magic + Intellectual Superiority + Augmentation + Radiant Visage + Obscure.<br>
<br>
Although I have a history of refusing a lot of donations, I will accept them at times; offering a donation (whether I accept them or not) can earn you a place in my List of People to Help Whenever Possible.  I expect that other people feel much the same way about this.<br>
<br>
All the people who do these other things usually end up on /ignore or my List of People to Never Help.<br>
<br>
And, one last thing, even if you don't roleplay I'd ask that you respect the fact that I do Mr. Evil I Want Buffs.  I'm a Fair Elf.  I abhor undead and evil.  I reserve the right to take offense to your evil god, your slaying of innocent and otherwise peaceful creatures (whether they give faction hits or not), your class, and your behaviour.  You reserve the right to take offense to anything about me.  I ask only that you don't start /shouting that I'm every kind of blankety-blank just because I won't track for you, or buff, heal, or port you.<br>
<br>
And please don't waste my time or yours explaining how /role works; it hides your class and level and race, but shows your guild if you have one.  It's generally used by Druids and Wizards to avoid "please port/tl me" and serves absolutely no purpose other than to go anonymous while still displaying your guild affiliation.  Typing /role does not make you a roleplayer and there is no law that says roleplayers must use it.  Don't waste our time telling me to go to the Firiona Vie server either; it didn't exist when my chars were "born" and I have community ties where I am.<br>
<br>
Soapbox anyone? <p><hr>
